0003  -219.064542 </code></pre>  <p>My current script is:</p>  <pre><code>#!/usr/bin/perl  use strict; use warnings;  print "Name of all total energy containing file:\n"; my $energy_file = &lt;STDIN&gt;; chomp $energy_file;  my $inputfile_energy = $energy_file;  open (INPUTFILE_ENERGY, "&lt;", $inputfile_energy) or die $!;  print map $inputfile_energy-&gt;[0], sort { $a-&gt;[1] &lt;=&gt; $b-&gt;[1] } map { [ $_, /(\d+)$/ ] } &lt;INPUTFILE_ENERGY&gt;;  close $inputfile_energy; </code></pre>  <p>At this point I am just trying to get the energy with their names to print to the correct order. Then I will loop through the files in the directory and when the name matches with the sorted energy names it will be renumber.    </p>